1C X pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "b55389af98ef499ae41f9ecd112aa7235cea71a032faafcf49e38980cf408cb9"]
[Category "Defense"]
[Difficulty "beginner"]
[SkillPath "defense/opening_leads"]
[Student "W"]
{The bidding has been as shown. The contract is 1\C doubled 

Lead the \C5.

There is only one reason partner would pass your takeout double - he has a great \C suit and he expects to inflict a large penalty.

What he wants do do is pull East's trumps so your high card winners don't get ruffed by East. The way you can help him do that is to start with a trump lead.

With the trump lead East might not make more than three tricks.}
[Play "W"]C5

